11 July 2020 Government wishes to update the nation on the arrangement for the Special Official Funeral of the late Regent of the Royal House of the amaRharhabe, Her Majesty Queen Noloyiso Sandile who passed away on the 8th of July 2020. 1.     Burial and Funeral service Her Majesty will be buried on Sunday, 12 July 2020 at Mngqesha Great Place, King William’s Town at 07h00. This will be followed by a funeral service at 08h00. 2.     Condolences Those who wish to send messages of condolence to the family and friends of the Queen are encourage to utilised the e-condolence book available on: condolences@gcis.gov.za. 3.     Live Feed Government will stream live the burial and funeral proceedings on the following platforms: Twitter: https://twitter.com/GovernmentSA Facebook: https://web.facebook.com/GovernmentZA YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared a Special Official Funeral Category 1 for the late Queen Noloyiso Sandile. Enquiries: Phumla WilliamsGCIS Director-General Cell: 083 5010 139